        <section id="suggested-changes">
            <h3>Suggested Changes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Ensure stories are personal and not made up by AI.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="risks">
            <h3>Risk and Mitigation</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Bias or discrimination in presentation materials - Cross-validation for other ideas from humans.</li>
                <li>Research proprietary issues - Add to policy list.</li>
                <li>Accuracy - Cross-validation, sources, and explanation of recommendations.</li>
                <li>Privacy concerns - Strip private info.</li>
                <li>Fake stories - Ensure authenticity and human oversight.</li>
                <li>Reduce human workload by 30%.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="policies">
            <h3>Policy Suggestions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Pay royalties to providers of research/statistics.</li>
                <li>Limit AI usage to 30% (gradual migration).</li>
                <li>Maintain cross-validation, sources, and explanations.</li>
                <li>Keep humans in the loop for decision-making and refinement.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="prompts">
            <h3>Prompts</h3>
            <h4>Visualize the Results</h4>
            <p>
                <strong>Description:</strong> Creates an image of what your solution to the need will look like by interactively asking questions about the purpose of the image. It uses DALL-E to create the image.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Prompt:</strong>
                "Create a visually striking image inspired by a persuasive speech, focusing on the key elements provided below. Answer the following questions to refine the image prompt for maximum impact:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Task:</strong> What is the primary goal of the image?</li>
                <li><strong>Context:</strong> What is the setting or backdrop of the image?</li>
                <li><strong>Example:</strong> Are there specific visual elements or metaphors mentioned in the speech?</li>
                <li><strong>Persona:</strong> Who is the target audience for this image?</li>
                <li><strong>Format:</strong> What format should the image take?</li>
                <li><strong>Tone:</strong> What is the emotional tone of the image?</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Once these details are provided, I will synthesize them into a cohesive prompt for DALL-E to create the image.
            </p>
